In Git, Porcelain and Plumbing describe two levels of commands, based on who they are meant for.

1> Plumbing - Low-level internal commands used by Git itself.
example :-> git hash-object
            git cat-file
            git update-index
            git write-tree
            git commit-tree

2> Porcelain - High-level user commands meant for daily use.
examples :->  git status
              git add
              git commit
              git push
              git pull
              git clone
